{"_id":"a4UMj8gN3S7hwlZR","name":"Divine Force Specifics & Options","content":"<p>Though the base Divine Force rules cover most spells, various modifications apply to more complicated spells.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>One Target: </strong>The spell targets only you, even if it normally allows more targets. Some feats let you affect more creatures.</li>\n<li><strong>Variable Actions: </strong>Some spells have different effects based on the number of actions you spend to cast them. You choose whether to use the effects of the 1- or 2-action version of the spell when you use Divine Force. A spell has to take exactly 1 or 2 actions; you can’t use Divine Force with a spell that takes a free action, reaction, or 3 or more actions.</li>\n<li><strong>Metamagic: </strong>You typically can’t use metamagic with Divine Force because metamagic requires the next action you take to be Cast a Spell, and Divine Force is a combined activity that doesn’t qualify</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>DIVINE FORCE OPTIONS</h3>\n<p>The following cantrips and 1st-level spells target the caster and can therefore be used with Divine Force. This list can get you started picking your spells</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cantrips: </strong>Bolster, @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.W02bHXylIpoXbO4e]{Bullhorn}, @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.izcxFQFwf3woCnFs]{Guidance}, @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.WBmvzNDfpwka3qT4]{Light}, @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.TVKNbcgTee19PXZR]{Shield}, @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.AUctDF2fqPZN2w4W]{Sigil}</li>\n<li><strong>1st-Level Spells: </strong>@Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.XSujb7EsSwKl19Uu]{Bless}, @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.wdA52JJnsuQWeyqz]{Harm}, @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.rfZpqmj0AIIdkVIs]{Heal}, @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.TFitdEOpQC4SzKQQ]{Magic Weapon}, @Compendium[pf2e.spells-srd.dINQzhqGmIsqGMUY]{Mending}</li>\n</ul>","folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"gKRAixZcnc2H4VRx":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.vBFI0HMD4xltVolK"}}}
